@ThinkingandTinkering just seems like a lot of extra steps, and a bit of waste of space, to make it take up a larger area then it has to.

If its all inline it has no need to take up space on the ground. It can all fit in the pipe, with a couple lines running to whatever power storage you have for the energy.

See I live in an apartment, and I've been being learning all about the need to minimize the space taken up by projects, while maximizing their benefits. And making the best of the limited space I have. So I guess its influencing my thinking.
